    "plot": [
        "_Shikara_ (qv) is the story of resilience in the face of insurmountable odds. It's also the story of a love that remains unextinguished through 30 years of exile. A timeless love story in the worst of times.",
        "In 1990, 4 lakh Kashmiri Pandits (Hindus) were forced to leave their home under the threat of life. Till today, they continue to live as refugees in their own country, in small refugee camps in the city of Jammu. Vidhu Vinod Chopra's '_Shikara_ (qv)' follows the story of Shiv and Shanti, two Kashmiri Pandits, chronicling their survival through 30 years of exile. In the current season of hate, love is all that keeps hope alive.",
        "Dr Shiv and his wife are living in Jammu transit camp since last 28 years since tensions erupted between Muslims and Kashmiri Pandits, he has been writing letters to American President hoping to get reply someday.Shiv is called to Agra as the president is visiting India while living in their suite flashback revels how Shiv and Shanti met during an on ongoing film shoot in Kashmir an both married soon while he was pursuing Phd.Shiv with his lifetime savings manages to purchase a house and Shanti names it _Shikara_ (qv) things are going well until tensions arise between Muslims and Kashmiri Pandits forcing many Kashmiri Pandits to leave Kashmir.::alex.mjacko@gmail.com"
